      fix(dart): allow `. ... .` in chained method calls
      
      The polyglot `dots_method_chaining` pattern
      
          $X = $O.foo(). ... .bar(). ...
      
      did not parse with Dart's grammar: the base `selector` rule accepts
      `_assignable_selector | argument_part | type_arguments | !`, and none
      of those can match a bare `...` between chain segments. Pattern authors
      had to write a Dart-specific override or accept a `dots_method_chaining`
      exception in the GA maturity tests for Dart.
      
      Add a `semgrep_dot_ellipsis_selector` rule (`seq('.', $.semgrep_ellipsis)`)
      to the semgrep-dart extension and graft it into `selector` so it
      interleaves naturally between real `.foo()` / `.bar()` calls.
      
      Add `lang/dart/test/ok/chained_call_ellipsis.dart` to pin the new
      parse path.
